-- Rosneft, VTB and Norilsk Nickel May Move: Russian Equity Market Preview
-- Stephen Bierman
-- 2010-07-05T20:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/rosneft-vtb-and-norilsk-nickel-may-move-russian-equity-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are from the previous close.  
 Russia’s ruble-based Micex Index rose 0.3 percent yesterday
to 1,292.19 in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS rose 0.1
percent to 1,318.  
 OAO Rosneft  (ROSN RX): Crude oil declined for the sixth
straight day. Russia’s largest oil producer fell 0.7 percent to
187.67 rubles on the Micex Stock Exchange.  
 VTB Group  (VTBR RX): Russia’s second biggest lender has
hired BNP Paribas SA and VTB Capital to organize the sale of
bonds denominated in Swiss francs, according to a banker
familiar with the transaction. VTB rose 2.2 percent to 0.075
ruble.  
 OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel  (GMKN RX): Copper climbed for a
second straight day. Russia’s largest mining company gained 2.5
percent to 4,615.35 rubles.  
